00:50:24,416 --> 00:50:27,544
- Were her prayers answered?
- Well, the way all prayers are answered.

679
00:50:27,619 --> 00:50:29,553
Not in the way
she wanted.

680
00:50:29,621 --> 00:50:31,851
He turned up again when I was seven,
clean as a whistle...

681
00:50:31,923 --> 00:50:35,916
with a new wife named Dora...
took me to a new life in America.

682
00:50:35,994 --> 00:50:39,361
And, by the time
I made it back here, well...

683
00:50:39,431 --> 00:50:41,490
- She wasn't lighting candles anymore.
- Yeah.

684
00:50:41,566 --> 00:50:43,966
You know, that's the third
version you've told me.

685
00:50:44,035 --> 00:50:48,233
Well, that's the truth.

686
00:50:48,306 --> 00:50:51,173
- So is it true what they're saying?
- What are they saying?

687
00:50:51,242 --> 00:50:54,234
Well, they say
you're back in business.

688
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:58,713
- No?
- The only business I'm in, Roger...

689
00:50:58,783 --> 00:51:01,581
is the business
of recovery.

690
00:51:01,653 --> 00:51:04,144
Three weeks. I'm clean.

691
00:51:19,571 --> 00:51:22,335
[Shutter Clicks]

692
00:51:22,407 --> 00:51:25,808
Our daily bread,
forgive us our trespasses...

693
00:51:32,984 --> 00:51:35,418
Have you heard the story
of the Good Thief, Roger?

694
00:51:35,487 --> 00:51:37,751
- No. I'm not religious.
- No. Neither am I.

695
00:51:37,822 --> 00:51:40,655
But when my mother told it,
I guess it stuck.

696
00:51:40,725 --> 00:51:44,217
The Good Thief...
besideJesus on the cross...

697
00:51:44,295 --> 00:51:47,787
and Jesus said to him,
if I remember this right...

698
00:51:47,866 --> 00:51:50,926
"Tonight you will be
with me in paradise."

699
00:51:51,002 --> 00:51:54,494
And the thought that there was a place
in heaven for a thief always made me cry.

700
00:51:54,572 --> 00:51:56,506
[Chuckles]
You want to make me cry now?

701
00:51:56,574 --> 00:52:00,271
You gotta watch this cynicism, Roger.
It's too easy in that job of yours.

702
00:52:00,345 --> 00:52:04,543
- I'll work on my attitude.
- You should. You should.

703
00:52:04,616 --> 00:52:07,847
[Shutter Clicks]

704
00:52:09,087 --> 00:52:11,920
[Multiple Clicks,
Paulo Coughs]

705
00:52:13,191 --> 00:52:16,683
Bob. You saved my life,
but if you try something...

706
00:52:16,761 --> 00:52:19,855
- Try what?
- Do I have to spell it out?
I'll put you down for life.

707
00:52:19,931 --> 00:52:22,297
- You're a cop. That's what you do.
- What are you?

708
00:52:22,367 --> 00:52:25,632
I was good at thieving once, Roger,
and I may not be the Good Thief yet...

709
00:52:25,703 --> 00:52:28,399
but I am trying...
believe me, I am trying.

710
00:52:28,473 --> 00:52:30,407
Now if you excuse me.

711
00:52:30,475 --> 00:52:32,409
I have to
pay my respects.

712
00:52:32,477 --> 00:52:35,173
She was a good woman.
My mother.

713
00:52:55,667 --> 00:52:57,965
[Sighs]

714
00:53:04,475 --> 00:53:07,774
[Shutter Clicking,
Paulo Coughing]

715
00:53:14,352 --> 00:53:17,480
[Anne] What do you know?
It's the Candy Man.

716
00:53:17,555 --> 00:53:19,921
- [Said] Is that my new name?
- Yeah.

717
00:53:19,991 --> 00:53:22,357
Got a kiss for me
this fine evening?

718
00:53:22,427 --> 00:53:24,486
Yeah, sure.
[Chuckles]

719
00:53:30,969 --> 00:53:33,961
Your boyfriend Paulo...
what's he up to?

720
00:53:34,038 --> 00:53:37,439
- Works with Bob.
- On what?

721
00:53:37,508 --> 00:53:40,500
- Doesn't tell me.
- What's he working on, baby?

722
00:53:40,578 --> 00:53:43,979
That surprise.

723
00:53:44,882 --> 00:53:49,376
- On a safe.
- What safe?

724
00:53:49,454 --> 00:53:51,922
Give me first.

725
00:53:53,358 --> 00:53:55,826
[Clicks Lighter]

726
00:54:01,833 --> 00:54:03,767
A safe with 80 million.

727
00:54:05,403 --> 00:54:08,668
That's all I know.

728
00:54:18,750 --> 00:54:21,344
[Chattering In French]

729
00:54:27,558 --> 00:54:29,549
Got a light?

730
00:54:32,430 --> 00:54:36,025
That's it.
I'm giving up smoking.

731
00:54:36,100 --> 00:54:39,797
- Do you know nicotine's
more addictive than heroin?
- Really?

732
00:54:39,871 --> 00:54:41,805
Ask any junkie.

733
00:54:41,873 --> 00:54:43,864
- Are you done?
- Mm-hmm.

734
00:54:45,410 --> 00:54:47,378
- Anyone clock you?
- I don't think so.

735
00:54:47,445 --> 00:54:50,073
Guy with short hair with the ear piece.
Do you notice him?

736
00:54:51,149 --> 00:54:53,344
- Huh? Well, he noticed me.
- Yeah.

737
00:54:53,418 --> 00:54:55,409
Come on.

738
00:55:12,837 --> 00:55:15,328
- You want to see the vault?
- Yeah.

739
00:55:15,406 --> 00:55:17,772
I do my regular check
on their system.

740
00:55:17,842 --> 00:55:20,709
I plant my beetle.
Meanwhile, you enjoy the view.

741
00:55:20,778 --> 00:55:23,611
- From where?
- From the car behind.

742
00:55:23,681 --> 00:55:28,744
A reasonable picture, up to 100 meters.
Then it gets emotional.

743
00:55:28,820 --> 00:55:31,550
- Emotional?
- Kind of fuzzy.

744
00:55:31,622 --> 00:55:34,386
- Oh, emotional.
- [Engine Revving]

745
00:55:39,630 --> 00:55:43,361
[Man Speaking French]

746
00:55:48,940 --> 00:55:50,931
[French]

747
00:55:52,210 --> 00:55:54,201
- [French]
- [Gate Clicking]

748
00:56:17,502 --> 00:56:19,834
- He has some kind of fancy system.
- [Bob] Yes.

749
00:56:19,904 --> 00:56:21,838
- And there is nothing in that vault?
- Oh.

750
00:56:21,906 --> 00:56:24,397
I got a fine assist,
I guess we'll soon find out.

751
00:56:24,475 --> 00:56:26,466
[Car Door Slamming]

752
00:56:28,346 --> 00:56:30,337
Bon soir, monsieur.

753
00:56:31,516 --> 00:56:33,450
- [Turning Pages]
- Plans of the villa.

754
00:56:33,518 --> 00:56:36,180
- Where did you get them?
- Architectural Heritage Society. Very helpful.

755
00:56:36,254 --> 00:56:38,188
Security room, basement.

756
00:56:51,302 --> 00:56:53,270
[Whispering]
Don't you guys know me by now?

757
00:56:53,337 --> 00:56:56,101
- Procedure is procedure.
- Oh!

758
00:56:56,174 --> 00:57:00,804
Procedure is procedure.
Sounds like a techno band from Dusseldorf.

759
00:57:36,581 --> 00:57:38,572
[Beeping]

760
00:57:43,621 --> 00:57:46,681
- Oh.
- Wow!

761
00:57:46,757 --> 00:57:48,850
No fantasist he.

762
00:58:06,911 --> 00:58:10,039
[Rapid Beeping]

763
00:58:13,618 --> 00:58:15,552
Good.

764
00:58:29,166 --> 00:58:31,100
[Electronic Beeping]

765
00:58:46,484 --> 00:58:48,042
Could you...

766
00:58:57,595 --> 00:58:59,995
- Thank you.
- [Bob] Guess what that is.

767
00:59:00,064 --> 00:59:02,464
- What?
- The old Napoleonic sewers.

768
00:59:02,533 --> 00:59:04,899
They run downhill
towards the sea.

769
00:59:04,969 --> 00:59:08,302
That's our way in.
Turn that off. We can watch it later.

770
00:59:28,559 --> 00:59:31,653
Come on.
Do you think I'm blind or something...

771
00:59:31,729 --> 00:59:34,197
that I haven't noticed
what you're up to?

772
00:59:34,265 --> 00:59:37,564
- Yvonne...
- Men coming here to see you,
phone calls, everything.

773
00:59:37,635 --> 00:59:40,126
You're crazy.

774
00:59:40,204 --> 00:59:44,197
Bob, I haven't forgotten
that I opened this bar...

775
00:59:44,275 --> 00:59:46,209
with money you lent me.

776
00:59:46,277 --> 00:59:52,216
- So, if you need money now...
- You're mad, Yvonne.
What put that idea in your head?

777
00:59:52,283 --> 00:59:57,277
If you get yourself arrested,
you wouldn't survive, you bastard.

778
00:59:57,355 --> 01:00:02,156
Would you come and visit me inside,
bring me whiskey in a flask?

779
01:00:02,226 --> 01:00:06,492
- [Yvonne] It wouldn't be the first time.
- Do you know him?

780
01:00:08,566 --> 01:00:12,058
No. Never saw him before.

781
01:00:12,136 --> 01:00:16,038
Why do I
imagine I have?

782
01:00:16,107 --> 01:00:18,371
- Ciao.
- Take care.

783
01:00:21,379 --> 01:00:23,370
Turn around.
Follow me.

784
01:00:24,515 --> 01:00:28,508
- What's up?
- Behind me. You remember him?

785
01:00:35,893 --> 01:00:39,385
Philippa, hop in that doorway
and find out what his beef is.

786
01:00:44,568 --> 01:00:46,559
[Muffled Grunt]

787
01:00:47,571 --> 01:00:49,562
- What the hell?
- Oh.

788
01:00:49,640 --> 01:00:51,904
You think
he whacked Philippa?

789
01:00:51,976 --> 01:00:54,945
Nobody whacks Philippa.
You're twins, right?

790
01:00:55,012 --> 01:00:58,573
We're onto you.
Whoa, whoa.

791
01:00:58,649 --> 01:01:01,174
[Man]
What the fuck do you think you're doin'?

792
01:01:01,252 --> 01:01:04,847
- Get off!
- Philippa! Stop! Stop! Stop!

793
01:01:04,922 --> 01:01:08,688
- My arms are getting tired.
- Phil, be a bit more gentlemanly.

794
01:01:08,759 --> 01:01:12,330
This is Albert. That's Bertram
you're abusing. They're twins.

795
01:01:12,330 --> 01:01:13,262
This is Albert. That's Bertram
you're abusing. They're twins.

796
01:01:13,331 --> 01:01:15,265
Now, say you're sorry.

797
01:01:15,333 --> 01:01:17,858
- Sorry, Albert.
- The name's Bert.

798
01:01:17,935 --> 01:01:20,927
Let's go through it again.
This time pretend I'm slow.

799
01:01:21,005 --> 01:01:24,736
- Slow?
- Yeah, it means stupid, um, kind of.

800
01:01:24,809 --> 01:01:28,108
- It's simplicity itself.
- He's in charge of the deposits to the safe.

801
01:01:28,179 --> 01:01:30,113
They change
the combinations weekly.

802
01:01:30,181 --> 01:01:33,446
- I get the numbers. I make the deposits.
- He gives me the combinations.

803
01:01:33,517 --> 01:01:37,453
The night before the Grand Prix, while he's
in the manager's office, I'm on the floor.

804
01:01:37,521 --> 01:01:42,117
- The staff take me for him.
- He has access to the safe,
and my alibi is solid as a rock.

805
01:01:42,193 --> 01:01:45,754
I see. You've put a lot
of thinking into this.

806
01:01:45,830 --> 01:01:47,764
[Together]
Two heads are better than one.

807
01:01:47,832 --> 01:01:52,292
- So, what was your plan?
- [Sighs] Nothing like yours.

808
01:01:52,370 --> 01:01:55,828
- Infantile in comparison.
- We need help to move that kind of money.

809
01:01:55,906 --> 01:01:59,034
So, if you want in...

810
01:01:59,110 --> 01:02:02,807
- No one's ever seen you together.
- No one in Monte Carlo.

811
01:02:06,417 --> 01:02:10,183
- Give us a day or two to think about it.
Right, Paulo?
- Or three.

812
01:02:10,254 --> 01:02:12,779
You go out the back.
You go out the front.

813
01:02:12,857 --> 01:02:14,848
[Hinges Creak]

814
01:02:26,604 --> 01:02:28,765
- Crazy, boss, huh?
- Totally.

815
01:02:28,839 --> 01:02:32,900
But, you know, we want them
to think we want that safe.

816
01:02:32,977 --> 01:02:35,741
Twins. You see Roger's
following that?

817
01:02:35,813 --> 01:02:38,748
How's he gonna know
they're twins? Tell you what.

818
01:02:38,816 --> 01:02:41,785
Call him in a day or two.
Go through their plan again.

819
01:02:41,852 --> 01:02:44,946
- It has the benefit of originality.
- We've got that meeting.

820
01:02:45,022 --> 01:02:48,753
Yeah. You go out the back.
I'll go out the front. Try to lose Roger.

821
01:02:48,826 --> 01:02:50,817
Start without me
if you have to.

822
01:03:07,478 --> 01:03:11,471
Would you drive me, Roger? I have a meeting.
I'm attending Narcotics Anonymous.

823
01:03:11,549 --> 01:03:13,483
That was your support group
up there?

824
01:03:13,551 --> 01:03:17,885
- Yeah.
- [Engine Starts, Runs]

825
01:03:20,057 --> 01:03:23,857
You're welcome to join me. You should
support me in my battle against my addictions.

826
01:03:23,928 --> 01:03:25,862
Your addictions being...

827
01:03:25,930 --> 01:03:28,558
Gambling and narcotics.

828
01:03:28,632 --> 01:03:33,501
[Raoul] Okay, guys, imagine this is a vault.
All the alarms will be...

829
01:03:33,571 --> 01:03:35,835
coming in from here...

830
01:03:35,906 --> 01:03:37,840
And reinforced steel floor...

831
01:03:37,908 --> 01:03:42,004
- You know, every addict,
Roger, has an enabler.
- Nobody tells me anything.

832
01:03:42,079 --> 01:03:45,913
The one who, through no fault of their own,
maintains the addict in their habit.

833
01:03:45,983 --> 01:03:47,974
- Often needs the addict in their habit.
- [Chuckles]

834
01:03:48,052 --> 01:03:51,419
- Let me guess. Your enabler is...
- Is you.

835
01:03:51,489 --> 01:03:54,583
We're codependents, Roger.
We have been for years.

836
01:03:54,658 --> 01:03:56,717
I mean,
look at you, now.

837
01:03:56,794 --> 01:04:01,094
You're chasin' me, because you imagine
that I'm chasin' a big score.

838
01:04:01,165 --> 01:04:04,396
- [Laughs]
- And maybe the cure starts with you.

839
01:04:04,468 --> 01:04:08,495
- The cure?
- Yeah, because deep down
you want me to try that big one...

840
01:04:08,572 --> 01:04:10,563
if only to see
how I'd do it.

841
01:04:10,641 --> 01:04:13,872
There's nothing I can do
that'll convince you that I'm clean.

842
01:04:13,944 --> 01:04:15,912
It's unhealthy, Roger.

843
01:04:15,980 --> 01:04:18,949
- It means we're both hooked.
- [Raoul] Running through a tunnel...

844
01:04:19,016 --> 01:04:20,950
between the ceiling
and the floor...

845
01:04:21,018 --> 01:04:26,320
Bill packs these mikes... Make sure
you keep that needle below 90. Right, Vlad?

846
01:04:31,262 --> 01:04:34,390
[Bob] You wanna come up?
We can explore these issues further.

847
01:04:34,465 --> 01:04:37,127
- I haven't hit rock bottom yet.
- You will.

848
01:04:37,201 --> 01:04:40,261
- Are you sure?
- The cure starts now. Say it.

849
01:04:40,337 --> 01:04:44,171
- Say what?
- "My name is Roger. I'm an addict in recovery."

850
01:04:44,241 --> 01:04:49,076
- [Laughs] No, no. You say it.
- My name is Bob,
and I'm an addict in recovery.

851
01:04:49,146 --> 01:04:53,776
And today is the first day
of the rest of my life.

852
01:05:01,592 --> 01:05:04,254
[Woman]
My name is Michelle, and I am an addict.

853
01:05:04,328 --> 01:05:06,262
[Men And Women, Together]
Hello, Michelle.

854
01:05:06,330 --> 01:05:09,060
[Woman #2] My name is Anne,
and I am an addict.

855
01:05:09,133 --> 01:05:11,192
- [Together] Hello, Anne.
- My name is Case.

856
01:05:11,268 --> 01:05:13,202
- I am an addict.
- [Together] Hello, Case.

857
01:05:13,270 --> 01:05:16,137
- My name is Bob, and I'm an addict.
- [Together] Hello, Bob.

858
01:05:16,206 --> 01:05:18,197
My name is Francois,
and I'm an addict.

859
01:05:18,275 --> 01:05:22,211
[Together]
Hello, Francois.

860
01:05:22,279 --> 01:05:26,113
[Raoul] Paulo replaces the grill
andjoins Bob and me in the casino.

861
01:05:26,183 --> 01:05:29,380
We keep them busy there.
And... no smoking.

862
01:05:31,121 --> 01:05:35,615
Okay, guys: Mikes, needle, gas main,
grill and casino, eh?

863
01:05:35,693 --> 01:05:38,787
- And that's how it works in theory.
- Yeah, in theory.

864
01:05:38,862 --> 01:05:41,592
We rehearse this on Friday.
Did you explain everything?

865
01:05:41,665 --> 01:05:43,599
- [Raoul] Yeah, yeah.
- [Others Chattering]

866
01:05:43,667 --> 01:05:47,228
Well, we're gonna go in there at night,
all right? Everybody understand that?

867
01:06:17,835 --> 01:06:21,828
¢Ü¢Ü[Techno]

868
01:06:34,018 --> 01:06:37,579
So, Remi, have I gone up in the world,
or come down?

869
01:06:37,655 --> 01:06:39,919
From my perspective,
you're kind of standing still.

870
01:06:39,990 --> 01:06:42,390
You can't move
standing still?

871
01:06:42,459 --> 01:06:45,257
I think you should
value yourself more highly.

872
01:06:45,329 --> 01:06:47,263
Think he's right, Said?

873
01:06:47,331 --> 01:06:51,700
- Depends.
- Depends on what?

874
01:06:51,769 --> 01:06:55,535
- On what you're selling.
- Damaged goods. That's me.

875
01:06:55,606 --> 01:06:58,131
Would you prefer
to discuss this in private?

876
01:06:58,208 --> 01:07:01,974
Private? I like private.

877
01:07:07,885 --> 01:07:10,877
Come on, guys.
Come on.

878
01:07:27,971 --> 01:07:32,601
Location, the safe,
the 80 million francs.

879
01:07:32,676 --> 01:07:37,943
- And why should I tell you?
- Because I'll give you pleasant dreams.

880
01:07:38,015 --> 01:07:40,506
- Hmm.
- Look at this.

881
01:07:44,588 --> 01:07:46,852
[Straining]

882
01:07:59,737 --> 01:08:03,764
Paulo. Philippa.

883
01:08:03,841 --> 01:08:05,775
- Gas faucet.
- Right.

884
01:08:05,843 --> 01:08:09,802
Twist it left till it stops.

885
01:08:10,881 --> 01:08:12,815
Okay, boss.

886
01:08:14,017 --> 01:08:16,645
Aaah!
[Shudders]

887
01:08:21,892 --> 01:08:23,826
Hey...

888
01:08:24,895 --> 01:08:27,659
They're gonna rob...

889
01:08:27,731 --> 01:08:31,064
Bank of America,
fourth ofJuly.

890
01:08:31,135 --> 01:08:34,866
- Don't make fun of me, you bitch!
- Learn maturity from the dogs in the street?

891
01:08:34,938 --> 01:08:37,532
I know it's the casino
where they are, okay?

892
01:08:37,608 --> 01:08:40,577
The night before the Grand Prix
in Monte Carlo. Now, fuck off.

893
01:08:40,644 --> 01:08:42,635
- Chill it.!
- What?

894
01:08:44,448 --> 01:08:47,542
Anne?
How are you?

895
01:08:47,618 --> 01:08:48,846
- Okay.
- How are you?

896
01:08:48,919 --> 01:08:50,147
- Good.
- You okay?

897
01:08:59,630 --> 01:09:01,564
- Here.
- Are you certain?

898
01:09:01,632 --> 01:09:04,760
- Yeah.
- It's my bag. I think it's lonely.

899
01:09:04,835 --> 01:09:07,599
- [Electronic Beeping]
- I miss you too.

900
01:09:07,671 --> 01:09:10,333
So, Vlad, that alarms
aren't mobilized?

901
01:09:10,407 --> 01:09:12,898
You still don't believe me?

902
01:09:12,976 --> 01:09:16,912
- What time is it, Raoul?
- Uh, 2:45.

903
01:09:16,980 --> 01:09:20,677
2:45. Okay.
Here goes.

904
01:09:20,751 --> 01:09:24,619
- ¢Ü¢Ü[Discotheque]
- A lovely kid like you
shouldn't be in a nightclub, you know?

