1237
01:41:33,278 --> 01:41:38,113
- 1873, sir.
- There's one way, of course,
the management could avoid paying.

1238
01:41:38,183 --> 01:41:41,983
- What are you implying, sir?
- It's unthinkable that a casino
would empty its own safe.

1239
01:41:42,054 --> 01:41:45,683
- [Rings]
- Its reputation...
- Its reputation is without peer.

1240
01:41:45,757 --> 01:41:50,694
- And your implication is beneath contempt.
- As I said, unthinkable.

1241
01:41:53,265 --> 01:41:55,699
- [French]
- [Phone Hanging Up]

1242
01:41:55,767 --> 01:41:59,066
- We will insist on a full investigation.
- You certainly should.

1243
01:41:59,138 --> 01:42:01,629
I mean, I would
if I was in your situation.

1244
01:42:01,707 --> 01:42:04,870
- Would you kindly put a "zock" in it, sir?
- A "zock"?

1245
01:42:07,212 --> 01:42:09,840
Put "zit"
in this mouth of yours.

1246
01:42:09,915 --> 01:42:13,373
Oh, you mean I should retire with my winnings
and keep my mouth shut?

1247
01:42:13,452 --> 01:42:17,548
- I mean shut the fuck up.
- Mmm.

1248
01:42:19,725 --> 01:42:22,489
Anne?

1249
01:42:33,472 --> 01:42:35,463
[Engine Stops]

1250
01:42:37,676 --> 01:42:41,407
- Wow!
- Ah, fuck! [Laughing]

1251
01:42:41,480 --> 01:42:46,008
- Yes! Yes! So, tell me again.
Which twin are you?
- The identical one.

1252
01:42:46,084 --> 01:42:49,053
- And which share do you get?
- He gets mine. I get his.

1253
01:42:49,121 --> 01:42:51,055
Do you always
share this way?

1254
01:42:51,123 --> 01:42:53,057
- Sharin' means carin'.
- Okay, okay!

1255
01:42:55,861 --> 01:42:59,160
- Hey, you won, you lunatic.
- [Chuckles]

1256
01:42:59,231 --> 01:43:01,859
It's not about winning, Roger.
It's about attitude.

1257
01:43:01,934 --> 01:43:04,835
Win or lose, you gotta
do 'em both with grace.

1258
01:43:04,903 --> 01:43:08,805
- You learn that in recovery?
- Change the things you can.
Accept the things you can't.

1259
01:43:08,874 --> 01:43:10,865
And learn the wisdom
to know the difference.

1260
01:43:10,943 --> 01:43:14,401
Ah, so, what's the difference between
a run of luck and a casino heist?

1261
01:43:14,479 --> 01:43:17,346
[Chuckles] Then again, Roger,
there are some eventualities...

1262
01:43:17,416 --> 01:43:19,350
that recovery
doesn't prepare you for.

1263
01:43:19,418 --> 01:43:21,352
No. No, no.
No difference, Bob.

1264
01:43:21,420 --> 01:43:23,411
- Very little, if you think about it.
- Well...

1265
01:43:23,488 --> 01:43:26,719
there'll be an investigation,
and I'll have to insist you stay in France.

1266
01:43:26,792 --> 01:43:29,260
- I'll never leave France.
- It could take some time.

1267
01:43:29,328 --> 01:43:31,819
- You'll have to talk to my lawyer.
- Who's your lawyer?

1268
01:43:31,897 --> 01:43:34,195
Have you any suggestions?

1269
01:43:34,266 --> 01:43:38,225
I have a friend of yours in custody
who'll need the best that money can buy.

1270
01:43:38,303 --> 01:43:43,536
I'd be careful, Roger. With this much money
she could sue you for damages.

1271
01:43:43,609 --> 01:43:45,600
Mm-hmm?

1272
01:43:53,485 --> 01:43:58,286
Yeah, yeah, yeah. You made it up to me.
Now, get off the phone. Yeah.

1273
01:43:58,357 --> 01:44:00,587
- You don't want to talk to Paulo, right?
- No.

1274
01:44:00,659 --> 01:44:05,187
- Tell him he doesn't live up
to my ideal of manhood.
- Is there anyone who does?

1275
01:44:05,264 --> 01:44:07,198
